               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-318-person2392">
                  THOMAS 
                  THOMPSON
               <interp inst="t18270913-318-person2392" type="surname" value="THOMPSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-318-person2392" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-318-person2392" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a cordwainer. On the 20th of August, I saw the prisoners in company together, about four yards from Simmons' house; the castors which I had seen on the window before, were in Smith's hands - I went and told Simmons; he then pursued - I returned to my shop; in a few minutes I saw them brought back. I have some little knowledge of Smith.</p>
               <p>EDWARD SIMMONS. I am a <rs id="t18270913-318-viclabel1774" type="occupation">broker and bookseller</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-318-victim2391 t18270913-318-viclabel1774"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18270913-318-crimeloc1775">Barbican</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-318-crimeloc1775" type="placeName" value="Barbican"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-318-crimeloc1775" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-318-off1772 t18270913-318-crimeloc1775"></join>. These castors were on the stall<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182709130134"></xptr>board at my window - I received information from Thompson - I went after the prisoners, and got beyond them - a neighbour gave me some information - I then went to a receiving-house, where I found the prisoners, with the custors on the table.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-318-person2393">
                  JAMES 
                  VINT
               <interp inst="t18270913-318-person2393" type="surname" value="VINT"></interp>
